1 Notwithstanding G.S. 150B-19(4), the rule adopted by the Commission pursuant to this section
2 shall be substantively identical to the provisions of subsection (c) of this section. Rules adopted
3 pursuant to this section are not subject to Part 3 of Article 2A of Chapter 150B of the General
4 Statutes. Rules adopted pursuant to this section shall become effective as provided in
5 G.S. 150B-21.3(b1), as though 10 or more written objections had been received as provided in
6 G.S. 150B-21.3(b2).
7 SECTION 4.(e) Sunset. – This section expires when permanent rules adopted as
8 required by subsection (d) of this section become effective.
9 SECTION 5. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
10 law.
